Prerequisites

On Server VM (Ubuntu):

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y apache2 php libapache2-mod-php
sudo a2enmod php*  # if needed on your image
sudo systemctl restart apache2


Create a tiny PHP site that uses PHP sessions (classic PHPSESSID cookie).

sudo mkdir -p /var/www/html/sessionlab
sudo nano /var/www/html/sessionlab/login.php


Paste:

<?php
session_start();
if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'POST') {
  $u = $_POST['username'] ?? '';
  $p = $_POST['password'] ?? '';
  // Demo only: fixed credentials for lab (shown in plaintext by design)
  if ($u === 'student' && $p === 'password123') {
    $_SESSION['user'] = $u;
    header('Location: /sessionlab/protected.php');
    exit;
  } else {
    $error = "Invalid login";
  }
}
?>
<!doctype html><meta charset="utf-8">
<h2>SessionLab Login (HTTP)</h2>
<?php if (!empty($error)) echo "<p>$error</p>"; ?>
<form method="POST" action="/sessionlab/login.php">
  <label>Username <input name="username"></label><br>
  <label>Password <input name="password" type="password"></label><br>
  <button type="submit">Login</button>
</form>


Create a “protected” page that requires the session:

sudo nano /var/www/html/sessionlab/protected.php

<?php
session_start();
if (!isset($_SESSION['user'])) {
  header('Location: /sessionlab/login.php'); exit;
}
?>
<!doctype html><meta charset="utf-8">
<h2>Welcome, <?php echo htmlspecialchars($_SESSION['user']); ?></h2>
<p>This is a protected resource served over HTTP using a session cookie.</p>
<a href="/sessionlab/logout.php">Logout</a>


Add a logout that clears the session:

sudo nano /var/www/html/sessionlab/logout.php

<?php
session_start();
session_unset();
session_destroy();
header('Location: /sessionlab/login.php');
